cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY. 

This paper proposes a method for neural architecture search (NAS) that integrates reinforcement learning and evolutionary algorithms. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as NAS is a subfield of machine learning. The proposed method is applied to image classification tasks, specifically CIFAR-10 and ImageNet, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of reinforcement learning in the method indicates that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The evolutionary aspect of the method suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of mutation controllers and the focus on efficient evolution suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
